Luo Yingxing is a visually impaired resident of southwest China's Guizhou Province. He is a self-taught musician who can play the drums, the guitar, the harmonica and other musical instruments on his back. He was forced to drop out of school when he was 14 because of an eye injury. Luo then taught himself to play music with a magnifying glass. He also goes live on social media where he uses music and singing to promote his hometown.